hen in Ammo slot. You might want to be careful about paying too much before you look into ammo slot items.<br><br><br>Oh, and a few suggestions:<br>Velious/Rightious armor instead of the DW armor. (don't swap out DW helm for RP helm though)<br><br>Breastplate: At least Valorium/Barbed Ringmail.<br><br>Neck: You could try for that Mithaniel-somethingorother neckpiece that drops in POA. It's not Mithaniel-worshippers only <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  15 AC with a stat or 2.<br><br>A lot of your ideas for upgrades seem reasonably solid pieces of equipment (I'd love to have your gear to upgrade out of lol) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umrbone1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MrBone1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 118<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/17/02 7:48:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=225.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 54 - Equipment Check Please</span><hr size=1> Raid Arena in thurg and replace the crusty stuff with Runed Protectors.  Try to get on a POA raid and pick up a Symbol of Marr (15 AC, 5 str/wis).  Also, a goranga idol would be a decent range item that is easy to get.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/18/02 10:13:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=225.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 54 - Equipment Check Please</span><hr size=1> What island/mobs does the Symbol of Marr drop from?  How common is it as drops go?  My guild is heading there soon and I'd like to keep an eye out for it while we're there hehe.<br><br>Aalek<br>59 Knight<br>Reign in Power <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/18/02 11:04:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=225.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 54 - Equipment Check Please</span><hr size=1> I believe someone mentioned that it drops pretty commonly on Isle 1...  Don't know more than that. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umrbone1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MrBone1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/18/02 12:53:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=225.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 54 - Equipment Check Please</span><hr size=1> It drops everywhere.  If you go on a raid and make it to the third isle (which is very easy, mobs are still non KOS) you're pretty much guaranteed to see a Symbol of Marr. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugiggsgoodknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Giggs Goodknight</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/18/02 1:27:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=225.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.subside.com/aurora/screenshots/battles/Auroravsgoblins.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 54 - Equipment Check Please</span><hr size=1> I've seen the Symbol of Marr drop on every isle. <br><br>Stats are AC 15 Str/Wis +5<br><br>I think it's a nice item. I still wear one at level 60. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 185<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/18/02 2:38:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=225.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 54 - Equipment Check Please</span><hr size=1> You Dwarven Paladins really need to learn more about Enchanted/Imbued Brellium Plate. (Dwarven Cultural Plate)  So here goes!<br><br>Mask AC 8, STA 4, WIS 2, sv fire 1, sv magic 4, wt 2.0 <br>Collar AC 10, STR 4, STA 6, WIS 3, sv vs fire 1, sv vs magic 4, wt 4.5 <br>Belt AC 10, STR 4, STA 6, WIS 3, sv magic 3, sv fire 2, wt 4.5 <br>Bracer AC 11, STR 4, STA 4, WIS 2, sv fire 1, wt 4.5 <br>Cloak AC 11, STR 6, STA 6, WIS 4, sv magic 5, sv fire 3, wt 4.1 <br>Boots AC 15, STR 8, STA 8, WIS 4, sv magic 4, sv fire 4, wt 7.5 <br>Gauntlets AC 13, STR 4, STA 4, WIS 4, sv magic 4, sv fire 4, wt 5.5 <br>Pauldrun AC 12, STR 4, STA 4, WIS 3, sv magic 2, sv fire 4, wt 5.0 <br>Vambraces AC 15, STR 5, STA 6, WIS 4, sv magic 2, sv fire 4, wt 7.0 <br>Helm AC 16, STR 4, WIS 4, STA 4, sv magic 5, sv fire 4, wt 5.0 <br>Greaves AC 16, STR 8, STA 8, WIS 4, sv magic 2, sv fire 4, wt 8.5 <br>Breastplate AC 28, STR 8, STA 10, WIS 4, sv fire 5, wt 11.5<br><br>Comparing each item above with what you have:<br>Mask: Toss-up... Extra Sta vs. Extra HP &amp; Mana.  Keep the Veil.<br>Collar: Brellium Plate wins by a landslide!<br>Belt: Yours has Haste... keep it.  Plus, the Axgoroth's Belt in ME is moderately easy to get if you get Haste in a different item.<br>Bracers: Brellium Plate wins, but you should get at least one Deepwater Bracer.<br>Cloak: Yours wins by the virtue of you having it already. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>Boots: Deepwater wins... but if you didn't have Deepwater, Brellium Plate would win.<br>Gauntlets: Gaunts of the Black have better AC, might get the Brellium for FR/MR gear.<br>Pauldrons: Brellium Plate wins by a landslide again!  Slighted Pauldrons from ME would be better though.<br>Vambraces: Deepwater wins, but if you didn't have Deepwater, Brellium Plate would win again.<br>Helm: Deepwater wins... and if you didn't have a DW Helm, I'd tell you to get one. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>Greaves: Brellium Plate wins by a landslide once more!<br>Breastplate: Brellium Plate wins... and even competes very well against Valorium &amp; Barbed Ringmail!<br><br>So, in summary, Enchanted/Imbued Brellium Plate is an excellent investment (if expensive in terms of skill &amp; Temper components) for Dwarven Paladins pre-Velious Quest armour.<br><br>More information can be found <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/secrets/recipes_smithing_dwarven.htm">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.<br><br>Plus, if/when you outgrow it, you can sell it to the twink Gnome &amp; Halfling Paladins. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/20/02 11:06:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=225.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 54 - Equipment Check Please</span><hr size=1> Just boss mobs or any mob?  We did a PoA raid once before up to the point for me to do my FA turnin, and I'm pretty sure we didn't see one (maybe I was afk for it /shrug, that was a rough day with RL stuff going on, I was popping in and out a lot).<br><br>We're going back soon I suppose I'll wait and see, I was actually thinking if it drops on the first few islands I might just go up ahead of time with a single group and try for one.<br><br>Thanks for the info.<br><br>Aalek<br>59 Knight<br>Reign in Power<br>Torvonnilous <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showNextMessage?topicID=225.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddR